description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note: previous applicants need not apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Psychotherapist – Group &amp; Individual: Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coventry &amp; Warwickshire Partnership Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Olive Tree, since it opened in 2005, has become a highly successful personality disorder service and is a fully integrated element of Coventry &amp; Warwickshire Partnership Trusts’ mental health service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With our innovative, dynamic and flexible approach, we aim to engage patients and deliver therapeutic interventions that are co-ordinated, consistent and clinically effective. We are looking to recruit a highly competent and clinically experienced candidate to join our team in providing specialist psychodynamic group and individual treatment. We provide psychotherapy in a multimodal approach combining care coordination and risk assessment with psychotherapeutic boundaries and analytic spirit. We are looking for a reflective and flexible team-player who can contribute to the continuing and evolving life of the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have substantial experience of working with personality disorder within a multidisciplinary team context and experience of working clinically with acute mental health patients in NHS settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have experience of carrying out assessments and producing written reports containing a psychologically based formulation and conceptual framework, to capture a patients needs and their suitability for Psychotherapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have an advanced capacity to psychologically process the work with complex patients and use communication skills effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify underlying group processes and dynamics and facilitate the understanding of conflicts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel you have the above skills and experience and want to know more about the post, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Bundyford - Interim Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;02476 961266 or 07500 605 667&lt;/p&gt;
